      • createJar

        public java.lang.String createJar(java.lang.String[] classes,
                                  float compilerVersion,
                                  java.util.jar.Manifest manifest,
                                  java.io.File jarDest,
                                  java.io.FileFilter filter,
                                  MissingJarResponseManager jarChoice)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a new jar.
        Parameters:
        classes - the classes to compile and put in this jar.
        compilerVersion - the java compiler version to use (1.6, 1.8, etc)
        manifest - the optional manifest to embed in this jar file.
        jarDest - the .jar file to write to.
        filter - a filter to control which files are added to the jar. By default all related files will be added to this jar (java files, class files, related resources), but you may want to exclude certain files.
        jarChoice - an optional model to decide what to do with dependencies.
        Returns:
        text describing what went wrong if compilation problems occurred. This returns null if this method was successful.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an IO problem occurs.
